<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Values for bit flags used to specify the mapping type for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// offloading.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecb"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">enum class</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecb">OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags</a> : uint64&#95;t &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// No flags</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbabfda9a63c9b7f11edcad1dc82149b98e"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbabfda9a63c9b7f11edcad1dc82149b98e">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;NONE</a> = 0x0,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Allocate memory on the device and move data from host to device.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba07cc0a659e39b41fe392c86bc11cd0ac"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba07cc0a659e39b41fe392c86bc11cd0ac">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;TO</a> = 0x01,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Allocate memory on the device and move data from device to host.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbad7002643132cb21f2109913d4c7d7c92"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbad7002643132cb21f2109913d4c7d7c92">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;FROM</a> = 0x02,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Always perform the requested mapping action on the element, even</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// if it was already mapped before.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbacdf40f046e81e20bed803a99988b9b69"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbacdf40f046e81e20bed803a99988b9b69">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;ALWAYS</a> = 0x04,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Delete the element from the device environment, ignoring the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// current reference count associated with the element.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbab4f086d24865ba8bfb2761e61ff7699c"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecbab4f086d24865ba8bfb2761e61ff7699c">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;DELETE</a> = 0x08,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The element being mapped is a pointer-pointee pair; both the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// pointer and the pointee should be mapped.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba67bb5754d8a930a0abad5e820064be2d"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba67bb5754d8a930a0abad5e820064be2d">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;PTR&#95;AND&#95;OBJ</a> = 0x10,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This flags signals that the base address of an entry should be</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba732ea9b86ca290313731e1222052ce1b"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba732ea9b86ca290313731e1222052ce1b">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;TARGET&#95;PARAM</a> = 0x20,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Signal that the runtime library has to return the device pointer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// in the current position for the data being mapped. Used when we have the</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba5809336cf30db5e602df51986460f649"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba5809336cf30db5e602df51986460f649">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;RETURN&#95;PARAM</a> = 0x40,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This flag signals that the reference being passed is a pointer to</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba9a9d48223bc0be9fc043db7cf39c5a70"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba9a9d48223bc0be9fc043db7cf39c5a70">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;PRIVATE</a> = 0x80,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="223"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Implicit map</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="225"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Close is a hint to the runtime to allocate memory close to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the target device.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba8221e00e56f2d3110db685d1724a67c0"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba8221e00e56f2d3110db685d1724a67c0">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;CLOSE</a> = 0x400,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="228"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// 2048 is reserved for compatibility with XLC.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="229"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Produce a runtime error if the data is not already allocated.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="230" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba7760c660d78f028453fcb93a578d33bb"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a02d7a52c47f2d71a111aef9d4fb70ecba7760c660d78f028453fcb93a578d33bb">OMP&#95;MAP&#95;PRESENT</a> = 0x1000,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00231" /><CodeLine lineNumber="231"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Increment and decrement a separate reference counter so that the data</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="232"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// cannot be unmapped within the associated region.  Thus, this flag is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00233" /><CodeLine lineNumber="233"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// intended to be used on &#39;target&#39; and &#39;target data&#39; directives because they</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="234"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are inherently structured.  It is not intended to be used on &#39;target</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="235"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// enter data&#39; and &#39;target exit data&#39; directives because they are inherently</span></CodeLine>
